<DOC><DOCNO> AP881209-0149 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-09-88 1813EST</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-BRF--Reagan-Trip     12-09 0151</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Reagan-Trip,150</SECOND><HEAD>Reagan to Speak at University of Virginia</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   President Reagan will make a major foreignpolicy address next Friday at the University of Virginia, the WhiteHouse announced.   Presidential spokesman Marlin Fitzwater said Friday that Reaganwould travel by helicopter to the UVA campus in Charlottesville,Va., about 125 miles southwest of Washington, and give the speech tosome 700 students and faculty in Cabbell Hall.   It will likely be Reagan's last major speech before he and firstlady Nancy Reagan fly to Los Angeles on Dec. 23 at the start of atwo-week Christmas and New Year's vacation there and in PalmSprings, Calif.   The speech in Charlottesville will be Reagan's second majoraddress of the week. The president will give a talk on domesticpolicy Tuesday to federal officials and business executives at theConstitution Hall of the Daughters of the American Revolution here.</TEXT></DOC>